## Executable prices — bid/ask mandatory for open/close

Per [CCXT ticker manual](https://github.com/ccxt/ccxt/wiki/Manual#ticker-structure):
tickers are **24h OHLCV stats**; `bid`/`ask` may be undefined. For **executable**
spread decisions use **order-book top** (`fetch_order_book` / `watch_order_book`
→ `bids[0]` / `asks[0]`), then ticker `bid`+`ask` when both are present.
**Never use `last` (or mid derived from `last`) for open/close triggers.**

| Context | Allowed price source |
| ------- | -------------------- |
| Screener row display, volume filter, chart | `last` |
| Screener `short_exchange_id` / `long_exchange_id` labels | bid/ask via `SpreadCalculator.best_executable_pair`; `last` only when bid/ask unavailable |
| Auto-trader open / accumulate | short **bid**, long **ask** → `SpreadCalculator.entry_spread_pct` |
| Auto-trader close | short **ask**, long **bid** → `SpreadCalculator.exit_spread_pct` |
| Strategy calculators | same as open (already bid/ask on `Quote`) |
| Opportunity `AutoTradingEngine` | order-book best bid/ask |

Implementation: `ExecutableSpreadResolver` in `application/` — cache book →
cache quote bid/ask → ticker bid+ask. REST `fetch_order_book_once` only when
`fetch_fresh=True` (open, close, DCA, funding protect, open-position monitor).
Candidate screener scan uses cached quotes only (no REST per symbol).

Venues listed in `Settings.screener_book_stream_exchanges` (default `mexc`) get
a dedicated `ScreenerBookStreamWorker` (`watch_order_book` WS) so screener spread
uses executable bid/ask even when `watch_tickers` omits them. REST
`fetch_order_book_once` runs only when cached entry spread ≥
`Settings.screener_rest_prefilter_spread_pct` (default 2%) **and** a leg on one of
those venues still lacks a cached book/quote — via
`ExecutableSpreadResolver.entry_spread_for_open` (does not block WS streams).

## Strategy term conventions

Use these terms consistently in strategy docs and payloads:

- `spread`: strategy edge in percent (basis / cross-price spread / funding-rate spread).
- `commission`: total fees for all strategy legs and both sides (open + close), in USDT.
- `funding`: net funding **cost** in USDT, `max(paid - received, 0)`.

For all two-exchange strategy calculations:

- Legs must be the same asset (`BASE/USDT` pair on both venues).
- Entry quotes: short leg `bid`, long leg `ask`.
- Exit quotes: short leg `ask`, long leg `bid`.

## Agent diagnostics — use scripts first (no trading)

**Hard rule**: When investigating exchange connectivity, account state, market
data, trade history, token identity, or paper-order anomalies — **run the
existing `scripts/` CLIs** before writing ad-hoc ccxt calls, raw REST/curl, or
one-off Python that duplicates project adapters. Always invoke via
`.venv\Scripts\python.exe` (see `.cursor/rules/tooling.mdc`).

**Never use cached files for analysis.** `closed_positions_cache.json` and any
other data files under `src/arbitrator/data/` are stale snapshots — **do not
read them to answer questions about trades, positions, PnL, or prices.**
Always fetch live data from exchanges:
- Closed positions / trade history → `scripts/trade_report.py --refresh`
  then read **`src/arbitrator/data/trade_report.json`** for analysis (xlsx is human-only).
  Never analyze from `closed_positions_cache.json` alone.
- Open positions / balances → `scripts/inspect_exchanges.py --json account`
- Tickers / order books → `scripts/inspect_exchanges.py --json ticker|orderbook`

| Situation | Script | Key flags |
| --------- | ------ | --------- |
| Credentials, USDT balance, positions, open orders | `scripts/inspect_exchanges.py` | `--json verify`, `--json account` |
| Public ticker, order book, symbol list | `scripts/inspect_exchanges.py` | `--json ticker`, `orderbook`, `list-symbols` |
| Open + closed positions (same pipeline as Orders UI) | `scripts/trade_report.py` | **always `--refresh`**; agent reads `data/trade_report.json` |
| Paper orders vs OHLCV, spread/PnL audit | `scripts/audit_paper_orders.py` | read-only by default |
| FF strategy backtest on historical OHLCV | `scripts/backtest_ff.py` | public data; no keys |
| Cross-exchange token contract identity | `scripts/check_token_identity.py` | `--output report.md` |

Primary exchange inspector: skill
`.cursor/skills/exchange-read-only-inspect/` → `ReadOnlyExchangeInspector`
(`verify`, `account`, `ticker`, `orderbook`, `list-symbols`). Add `--json` on
`inspect_exchanges.py` for machine-readable agent output.

Example commands (repo root, Windows):

```text
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/inspect_exchanges.py --json verify
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/inspect_exchanges.py --json account --exchange bitget
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/inspect_exchanges.py --json ticker --exchange mexc --symbol BTC/USDT:USDT
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/trade_report.py --refresh --last 10
# agent: parse src/arbitrator/data/trade_report.json
# human: open src/arbitrator/data/trade_report.xlsx
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/audit_paper_orders.py
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/check_token_identity.py
```

**Forbidden for agents** without explicit user approval:

- `open_market_position`, `close_market_position`, `create_order`,
  `cancel_order`, `set_leverage`, or external trading MCP tools.
- `scripts/audit_paper_orders.py --fix` (mutates `paper_orders.json`).
- External exchange MCP servers that expose trading tools (see skill).
